ğŸ‘‰ Sorting Functionality:
âœ… Users can sort their transaction history either in ascending or descending order based on transaction amounts.

â­ Array Methods Used â­
ğŸ‘‰ reduce(): Utilized to calculate account balance, total deposits, total withdrawals, and interest earned.
ğŸ‘‰ filter(): Used to filter deposits, withdrawals, and loan eligibility based on transaction amounts.
ğŸ‘‰ map(): Applied to calculate interest earned on deposits.
ğŸ‘‰ push(): Employed to add new transactions to the transaction history array.
ğŸ‘‰ splice(): Utilized for account deletion when closing an account.
ğŸ‘‰ forEach(): Used for various iterations, such as displaying transaction history and creating user usernames.
